{
  "part1": "First 8 seconds. Scene opens with the East/Southeast Asian male in his late 20s to early 30s seated slightly to the right of center in the frame, in a relaxed posture leaning slightly left in a vintage-style grey-brown leather office chair with wooden accents and chrome frame. He wears a heather grey short-sleeved crew-neck t-shirt with natural folds and dark navy blue sweatpants. His dark brown/black medium-length messy hair is pushed back with some strands falling on his forehead. His warm medium-tan skin with natural pores and slight stubble is softly lit by natural light from a large window to his left, casting gentle shadows along the right side of his face. He holds a matte black Baseus MC1 Pro wireless earbuds charging case naturally in his left hand, palm facing camera, fingers spread with thumb on bottom edge and index on the left side, angled slightly right revealing the white 'Baseus' text on the front. The blurred background shows the wooden desk with books, phone, resistance bands, green houseplants on shelves, and window with white frame and light-colored buildings outside. The camera is at a slightly below eye-level medium shot handheld selfie framing, with slight natural shake. He looks softly upward and left of the camera, smiling gently with mouth slightly open showing upper teeth with a gap, relaxed eyebrows with crinkles at eyes’ corners. He begins speaking casually in Indonesian style, calling out a common frustration about earbuds. Duration: 8 seconds.",

  "part2": "Continuation seamless from second 8 onward. The same male character, outfit, posture, and exact environment remain unchanged with identical natural soft lighting, camera angle, focus, and handheld selfie slight movement. He shifts perspective lightly, introducing the Baseus MC1 Pro earbuds as the solution, highlighting the SuperBass 2.0 feature naturally while holding the charging case in the same manner. He adds soft social proof hinting at satisfaction and urgency and ends the casual, honest talk with the required CTA in Indonesian: \"Klik keranjang kiri bawah ya!\" The product placement remains perfectly consistent with fingers spread and front facing the camera showing the brand name. The atmosphere stays calm, casual, and inviting throughout. Duration: 8-12 seconds."
